<span style=3D"font-size:20px"><strong>Why should we save energy?</strong><=
/span>

<p><span style=3D"color:#c0392b"><strong>Over the past two years, utility c=
osts have risen sharply, with electricity prices increasing by 35% and gas =
prices by 30%.</strong></span> The rising cost of utilities, which now acco=
unt for a significant portion of the dormitory operating expenses (32% as o=
f two years ago), continues to place financial strain on our dormitory mana=
gement.&nbsp;Despite a gradual increase of approximately 10% in dormitory f=
ees from the Fall 2023 semester to the Spring 2024 semester, challenges hav=
e arisen in maintaining student welfare due to a significant rise in utilit=
y expenses, which make up the second-largest portion of dormitory operating=
 costs (around 32% two years ago), following personnel expenses (around 39%=
 two years ago).&nbsp;The Student Life team has made various efforts to red=
uce operating costs while maintaining student welfare, such as reducing sta=
ff (20 members through natural attrition), discontinuing low-participation =
programs like newspaper subscriptions and cable TV services, diversifying s=
uppliers for frequently replaced items like chairs and mattresses, and opti=
ng to clean rather than replace furniture when possible. Despite these meas=
ures, ongoing deficits continue to pose challenges, making it difficult to =
fully address needed facility improvements, <span style=3D"color:#c0392b"><=
strong>which has gradually impacted the welfare and benefits available to r=
esidents</strong></span>. To help alleviate this situation, we kindly ask f=
or your voluntary participation in energy conservation. By reducing unneces=
sary energy waste, we can work together toward more sustainable environment=
al practices and improve the living environment in our dormitories.</p>
